{
  "message": "test(patterns): gemini.model.used anchor coverage + near-miss goldens (ft-8ku8p)\n\ncrates/frankenterm-core/src/patterns.rs:2050 ships gemini.model.used\nwith three broad anchors: \"Using model\", \"Model:\", \"Switched to model\",\nthen extracts a gemini-* identifier via regex. Prior corpus coverage\nwas positive-only with one sample per alt phrasing (model_used.txt,\nmodel_used_alt.txt), which left the false-positive boundary unpinned\n\u2014 generic help/config text containing \"Model:\" or \"Using model\" was\nfree to regress into a spurious match without any test noticing.\n\nFive new fixture pairs under tests/corpus/gemini/:\n\nPositive goldens (anchor coverage):\n- model_used_model_label.{txt,expect.json}:\n    \"Model: gemini-2.5-pro\" \u2014 fires on \"Model:\" anchor.\n- model_used_switched.{txt,expect.json}:\n    \"Switched to model: gemini-2.5-flash\" \u2014 fires on third anchor.\n- model_used_whitespace.{txt,expect.json}:\n    multi-line \"Using model:\\n    gemini-2.5-pro-preview-05-06\"\n    \u2014 covers continuation-line layout the CLI actually emits.\n\nNegative goldens (false-positive fence):\n- model_used_near_miss.{txt,expect.json}:\n    gemini help text with \"Using model:\", \"Model:\", \"Switched to\n    model\" phrasings that describe the option rather than report a\n    selected model \u2014 must not fire. expect = [].\n- model_used_ansi_edge.{txt,expect.json}:\n    \"Model: <ansi>gemini-2.5-pro</ansi>\" \u2014 ANSI SGR escape bytes\n    injected around the model id break the byte-exact anchor\u2192regex\n    capture, same shape as oauth_required_ansi_edge.txt. expect = [].\n\nExtraction schema in every positive expect.json mirrors the existing\nmodel_used.expect.json verbatim (rule_id=gemini.model.used,\nagent_type=gemini, event_type=session.model, severity=info,\nconfidence=0.95) with only the extracted.model + matched_text\nvarying per fixture. Each anchor string is lifted literally from\npatterns.rs:2050.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
